                <h1>Stonewall Riots: A Turning Point for LGBTQ+ Rights</h1>
                <p>The Stonewall Riots, occurring in June 1969 at the Stonewall Inn in New York City, marked a pivotal moment in LGBTQ+ history. Following a police raid, patrons fought back, sparking days of protests and a collective push for gay rights. This event catalyzed the modern LGBTQ+ rights movement, inspiring activism and pride celebrations worldwide.</p>
